teran|D72|6}} ({{navy|UK}}).<ref name=NH044112/><ref name=Harbledown>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/860.html |title=Harbledown |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=20 February 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Imperio||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Kingdom of Italy|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was scuttled at Massawa. She was later salvaged.<ref name=NH044112/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Lichtenfels|1929|2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was scuttled at Massawa. Wreck scrapped in 1950.<ref name=NH044112/><ref>{{csr|register=MSI|id=5607043|shipname=Lichtenfels |accessdate=2 December 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Liebenfels||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was scuttled at Massawa. She was later salvaged by the British, repaired and entered service as ''Empire Nile.<ref name=Ships/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Marlene||2}} \n|flag={{Flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was torpedoed, shelled and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean ({{coord|8|15|N|14|19|W}}) by {{GS|U-124|1940|2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of 13 of her 60 crew.<ref name=NH044112/><ref name=StanA>{{cite web |url=http://www.mariners-l.co.uk/WWIStandardShipsA-K.htm#A |title=WWI Standard Built Ships A-K |publisher=Mariners |accessdate=8 May 2011}}</ref><ref name=Marlene>{{cite web |url=http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/861.html |title=Marlene |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=25 February 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Olva||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was scuttled at Massawa.<ref name=NH044112/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Greek torpedo boat|Proussa||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Greece|royalnavy}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[250t-class torpedo boat|''Kydoniai''-class torpedo boat]]  was bombed and sunk at [[Corfu]] by Italian air