raft with the loss of three crew.<ref name=NH044112/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|St Clement||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The coaster was bombed and sunk in the North Sea ({{coord|57|10|N|1|50|W}}) by Luftwaffe aircraft.<ref name=NH044112/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-76|1940|2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIB]] [[submarine]] was depth charged and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean south of Iceland ({{coord|58|32|N|20|15|W}}) by {{HMS|Arbutus|K86|6}}, {{HMS|Scarborough|L25|6}} and {{HMS|Wolverine|D78|6}} (all {{navy|UK}}) with the loss of one of her 43 crew. The survivors were taken as prisoners of war. }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==6 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=6 April 1941 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Antonia C.||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Kingdom of Italy|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was scuttled at [[Massawa]], [[Italian Somaliland]]. She was later salvaged.<ref name=NH044112/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Capitano Bottego||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Kingdom of Italy|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was scuttled off the [[Dahlak Islands]]. She was later salvaged.<ref name=NH044112/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMS|Comorin|F49|6}} \n|flag={{navy|UK}}\n|desc=The armed merchant cruiser caught fire in the Atlantic Ocean ({{coord|54|34|N|21|20|W}}) with the loss of 14 of her 419 crew. The survivors were rescued by {{HMS|Broke|D83|6}}, {{HMS|Lincoln|G42|6}} (both {{navy|UK}}) and {{SS|Glenartney||2}} ({{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}). ''Comorin'' was scuttled by HMS ''Broke''.<ref name=NH044112/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Daneland'' \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The trawler was bombed and sunk in the [[Irish Sea]] off [[Rathlin Island]], [[County Antrim]] by Luftwaffe aircraft. All crew were rescued.<ref name=NH044112/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship