 sank in the [[Baltic Sea]] off [[Griefswald, Rostock]], [[Mecklenburg-Vorpommern]].<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Pancration||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk at [[Milos]] by ''Luftwaffe'' aircraft.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=[[HMS Squirrel (1904)|''Sea-Serpent'']]\n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Battle of Greece]]: The [[yacht]] was bombed and sunk by ''Luftwaffe'' aircraft in the [[Aegean Sea]] between [[Syros]] and [[Souda]].<ref>{{cite book|last1=Halaris|first1=Dimitris|title=\u03a4\u03b1 \u039a\u03b1\u03c4\u03bf\u03c7\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac (The holder)|date=1997|publisher=S. Vogiatzis & Co OE|location=Athens|isbn=960-7364-16-3|page=278|language=Greek}}</ref>\n }}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Sifnos||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The coaster was bombed and sunk at [[Suda Bay]] by ''Luftwaffe'' aircraft. She was later salvaged by the Germans and repaired.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Sokratis||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=([[File: Red_Cross.png|40px]][[International Committee of the Red Cross|Red Cross]]): World War II: The hospital ship was bombed and sunk in the Gulf of Corinth at [[Antikyra]] by Luftwaffe aircraft.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Teti||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and damaged in Greek waters by Luftwaffe aircraft. She was beached to prevent her sinking.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Thassos|1919|2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk at [[Megara]] by Luftwaffe aircraft.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Thedol 2||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The coastal tanker was bombed, set on fire and sunk in the Gulf of Corinth at Antikyra by Luftwaffe aircraft.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Theodora|1917|2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The tanker caught fire, burned out and sank in the Gulf of Corinth at Antikyra as a result of  {{SS|Thedol 2||2}} ({{flag|Greece}}) being bombed by Luftwaffe aircraft and set on fire.  13 crewmen killed.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Thraki|1913|2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: the cargo ship was bombed and sunk in the Gulf of Corinth at [[Sombraina]] by Luftwaffe aircraft.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Vita|1914|2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=([[Image: Red_Cross.png|40px]][[International Committee of the Red Cross|Red Cross]]): World War II: The hospital ship was bombed and severely damaged in the [[Mediterranean Sea]] off [[Tobruk]], [[Italian Libya|Libya]] by [[Junkers Ju 87]] aircraft of III ''Staffeln'', [[Sturzkampfgeschwader 1]] and II ''Staffeln'', [[Sturzkampfgeschwader 2]], Luftwaffe and 96 & 236 Squadrons, [[Regia Aeronautica]]. {{HMAS|Waterhen|D22|6}} ({{navy|Australia|1913}}) rescued 498 people.<ref name=seekrieg194104/><ref name=NH044122/> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==23 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=23 April 1941 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''A.1'' \n|flag={{navy|UK}}\n|desc=World War II: The A lighter was bombed and damaged off Megara in the [[Mediterranean Sea]] by Luftwaffe aircraft. She was later scuttled.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Alberta|1900|2}} \n|flag={{Flag|Greece}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The passenger ship was bombed and sunk in the [[Saronic Gulf]] off [[Salamis Island]] by [[Luftwaffe]] aircraft.<ref name=Alberta>{{cite web |url=http://www.wrecksite.eu/wreck.aspx?31587 |title=SS Alberta (+1941) |publisher=Wrecksite |accessdate=20 December 2011}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Assimi||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The coaster was bombed and sunk at Krio