s |accessdate=9 February 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''N\u00e6raberg'' \n|flag={{flag|Faroe Islands}}\n|desc=World War II: The trawler was bombed and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean ({{coord|60|30|N|5|30|W}}) by Luftwaffe aircraft.<ref name=NH044112/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Nazario Sauro||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Kingdom of Italy|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was scuttled off the [[Dahlak Islands]]. She was later salvaged.<ref name=NH044112/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Nicolaou Zografia||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean ({{coord|57|10|N|12|30|W}}) by Luftwaffe aircraft. All 31 crew were rescued by {{HMS|Eskimo|F75|2}} ({{navy|UK}}).<ref name=NH044112/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Olga S||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean ({{coord|55|48|N|9|45|W}}) by Luftwaffe aircraft with the loss of four of her 33 crew. Survivors were rescued by {{HMS|Chelsea}} ({{navy|UK}}).<ref name=NH044112/><ref name=Crowninshield>{{cite DANFS | title = DD-134 | url = http://www.hazegray.org/danfs/destroy/dd134txt.htm |accessdate=15 January 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Riva Ligure||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Kingdom of Italy|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was scuttled at Massawa. She was later salvaged.<ref name=NH044112/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|HMY|Surf}} \n|flag={{navy|UK}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Battle of Greece]]: The naval yacht was bombed and sunk at Piraeus by Luftwaffe aircraft.<ref name=NH044112/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMS|Torrent|FY004|6}}  \n|flag={{navy|UK}}\n|desc=World War II: The naval yacht struck a mine and sank in the English Channel off [[Falmouth, Cornwall]] ({{coord|50|05|N|4|57|W}}) with the loss of over three crew.<ref name=NH044112/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Tripolitania||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Kingdom of Italy|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was scuttled off the [[Dahlak Islands]]. She was later salvaged.<ref name=NH044112/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Viking|1904|2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Battle of Greece]]: The salvage vessel was bombed and sunk at Piraeus by Luftwaffe aircraft.<ref name=NH044112/> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==7 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=7 April 1941 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Acropolis||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: [[Battle of Greece]]: The cargo ship was sunk at [[Piraeus]] by [[Luftwaffe]] bombing or the explosion of {{SS|Clan Fraser|1938|2}} ({{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}). The whole crew survived.<ref name=NH044112/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.historisches-marinearchiv.de/projekte/verluste_griechenland/ausgabe.php?lang=1&rubrik=%&where_value=256 |title=Acropolis |publisher=www.historisches-marinearchiv.de |accessdate=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|City of Roubaix||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Battle of Greece]]: The cargo ship was sunk at Piraeus by the explosion of {{SS|Clan Fraser|1938|2}} ({{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}).<ref name=NH044112/><ref name=seekrieg194104/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Clan Fraser|1938|2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Battle of Greece]]: Bombed and set on fire at [[Piraeus]], [[Greece]], by ''[[Luftwaffe]]'' [[Heinkel He 111]] bombers of II ''Staffel'', [[Kampfgeschwader 4]], the previous day, the {{sclass-|Cameron|steamship|0}} [[cargo ship]] sank with the loss of six crew members after her cargo of [[TNT]] exploded, wrecking the harbour.<ref name=NH044112/><ref name=seekrieg194104/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Cyprian Prince||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Battle of Greece]]: The cargo ship was damag