ip was bombed and damaged in Greek waters by Luftwaffe aircraft. She was beached to prevent her sinking.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Thassos|1919|2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk at [[Megara]] by Luftwaffe aircraft.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Thedol 2||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The coastal tanker was bombed, set on fire and sunk in the Gulf of Corinth at Antikyra by Luftwaffe aircraft.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Theodora|1917|2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The tanker caught fire, burned out and sank in the Gulf of Corinth at Antikyra as a result of  {{SS|Thedol 2||2}} ({{flag|Greece}}) being bombed by Luftwaffe aircraft and set on fire.  13 crewmen killed.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Thraki|1913|2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: the cargo ship was bombed and sunk in the Gulf of Corinth at [[Sombraina]] by Luftwaffe aircraft.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Vita|1914|2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=([[Image: Red_Cross.png|40px]][[International Committee of the Red Cross|Red Cross]]): World War II: The hospital ship was bombed and severely damaged in the [[Mediterranean Sea]] off [[Tobruk]], [[Italian Libya|Libya]] by [[Junkers Ju 87]] aircraft of III ''Staffeln'', [[Sturzkampfgeschwader 1]] and II ''Staffeln'', [[Sturzkampfgeschwader 2]], Luftwaffe and 96 & 236 Squadrons, [[Regia Aeronautica]]. {{HMAS|Waterhen|D22|6}} ({{navy|Australia|1913}}) rescued 498 people.<ref name=seekrieg194104/><ref name=NH044122/> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==23 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=23 April 1941 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''A.1'' \n|flag={{navy|UK}}\n|desc=World War II: The A lighter was bombed and damaged off Megara in the [[Mediterranean Sea]] by Luftwaffe aircraft. She was later scu