\n|utc_offset = +8\n|timezone_DST           = \n|utc_offset_DST        = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|37|26|34.08|N|78|34|36.8|E|region:CN|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation_footnotes    =  <!--for references: use <ref> </ref> tags-->\n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_ft           =\n<!-- Area/postal codes & others -------->\n|postal_code_type       =  <!-- enter ZIP code, Postcode, Post code, Postal code... -->\n|postal_code            =\n|area_code              =\n|website                = \n|footnotes              = \n}}\n'''Muji''' (Mu-chi; {{lang|ug|\u0645\u06c7\u062c\u0649 \u0628\u0627\u0632\u0649\u0631\u0649}} / {{lang|zh-hans|{{linktext|\u6728\u5409|\u9547}}}}, formerly {{lang|ug|\u0645\u06c7\u062c\u0649 \u064a\u06d0\u0632\u0649\u0633\u0649}} / {{lang|zh-hans|{{linktext|\u6728\u5409|\u4e61}}}}) is a [[Town (China)|town]] in [[Pishan County|Pishan/Guma County]], [[Hotan Prefecture]], [[Xinjiang]], China.\n[[File:Txu-pclmaps-oclc-22834566 g-7a.jpg|thumb|Map including Muji ({{w|Defense Mapping Agency|DMA}}, 1984)]]\n\n==History==\n[[File:China West 1906-08 Sven Hedin.jpg|thumb|Map including Muji ([[Royal Geographical Society|RGS]], early 20th century)]]\nBefore the Communist takeover, the area was called Muji District ({{lang|zh-hant|\u6728\u5409\u5340}}).<ref name=\"1997xzqhguma\"/>\n\nIn 1958, Bayi Commune ('[[Armed Forces Day (China)|August 1 Army Day]] Commune' {{lang|zh|{{linktext|\u516b|\u4e00|\u516c\u793e}}}}) was established.<ref name=\"1997xzqhguma\"/>\n\nIn 1978, Bayi Commune was renamed Muji Commune ({{lang|zh|\u6728\u5409\u516c\u793e}}).<ref name=\"1997xzqhguma\"/>\n\nIn 1984, Muji Commune became Muji Township ({{lang|zh|\u6728\u5409\u4e61}}).<ref name=\"1997xzqhguma\"/>\n\nIn 2012/3, Muji was changed from a [[Township (China)|township]] into a town.<ref name=\"xzqhguma\"/><ref name=\"govguma\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ps.gov.cn/zjps/psgk1/xzqh/content_31428|script-title=zh:\u884c\u653f\u533a\u5212|language=zh-hans|date=18 November 2018|accessdate=29 December 2019|quote={{lang|zh-hans|\u76ae\u5c71\u53bf\u8f966\u4e2a\u9547\u300110\u4e2a\u4e61\uff08\u5305\u62ec2\u4e2a\u6c11\u65cf\u4e61\uff09\uff1a\u56fa\u739b\u9547\u3001\u675c\u74e6\u9547\u3001\u9614\u4ec0\u5854\u683c\u9547\uff082015\u5e74\uff09\u3001\u514b\u91cc\u9633\u4e61\u3001\u79d1\u514b\u94c1\u70ed\u514b\u4e61\u3001\u6851\u682a\u9547\uff082016\u5e74\uff09\u3001\u6728\u5409\u9547\uff082013\u5e74\uff09\u3001\u4e54\u8fbe\u4e61\u3001\u6728\u594e\u62c9\u4e61\u3001\u85cf\u6842\u4e61\u3001\u76ae\u4e9a\u52d2\u739b\u4e61\u3001\u76ae\u897f\u90a3\u4e61\u3001\u5df4\u4ec0\u5170\u5e72\u4e61\u3001\u8d5b\u56fe\u62c9\u9547\u3001\u57b4\u963f\u5df4\u63d0\u5854\u5409\u514b\u65cf\u4e61\u3001\u5eb7\u514b\u5c14\u67ef\u5c14\u514b\u5b5c\u65cf\u4e61\u3002}}|website={{lang|zh-hans|\u76ae\u5c71\u53bf\u4eba\u6c11\u653f\u5e9c}}}}</ref>\n\n==Administrative divisions==\nKoxtag includes three [[residential community|residential communities]] and eighteen [[Village (China)|villages]]:<ref name=\"statsmuji\">{{cite web |url=http://www.stats.gov.cn/tjsj/tjbz/tjyqhdmhcxhfdm/2018/65/32/23/653223103.html |script-title=zh:2018\u5e74\u7edf\u8ba1\u7528\u533a\u5212\u4ee3\u7801\u548c\u57ce\u4e61\u5212\u5206\u4ee3\u7801\uff1a\u6728\u5409\u9547 |trans-title=2018 Statistical Area Numbers and Rural-Urban Area Numbers: Muji Town |language=zh-hans |publisher=[[National Bureau of Statistics of the People's Republic of China]] |date=2018 |accessdate=17 January 2020 |quote={{lang|zh-hans|\u7edf\u8ba1\u7528\u533a\u5212\u4ee3\u7801 \u57ce\u4e61\u5206\u7c7b\u4ee3\u7801 \u540d\u79f0 653223103001 121 \u5df4\u624e\u793e\u533a 653223103002 121 \u6587\u5316\u793e\u533a 653223103003 121 \u56e2\u7ed3\u793e\u533a 653223103200 220 \u9f99\u5c15\u6751\u6751\u59d4\u4f1a 653223103201 220 \u5170\u5e72\u6751\u6751\u59d4\u4f1a 653223103202 220 \u82f1\u5df4\u683c\u6751\u6751\u59d4\u4f1a 653223103203 220 \u9614\u7eb3\u8428\u4f9d\u5df4\u683c\u6751\u6751\u59d4\u4f1a 653223103204 220 \u5df4\u4ec0\u94c1\u70ed\u514b\u67